reviews.review_text: Wow, what a unique experience! Butter beef was a pleasant surprise and the rest of the food tasted so fresh and perfectly seasoned. No wonder why theres always a huge line up at this place. I dont blame them, its simply amazing.

Returning here after 10 years is definitely a surprise. The food is great but the lineup is even better, 1hr45min! Had to piece out after the first attempt and came back during a weekday after lunch time. I guess thats expected when you turn Michelin. Ordered the classic egg noodles and chicken wings, good as ever! Looks like the restaurant has been passed down the family generation but the taste is still classic. Highly recommended if youre in Vancouver and dont mind a wait or eating off hours. Worth it.

A friend visiting from San Francisco really wanted to go to Phnom Penh during her stay.  She came to the restaurant on her last visit and she said she needed to come to the restaurant again every time she visits Vancouver so we took her there for an early lunch this week. I remember coming here years ago and did not have a good impression of what I had but I m quite glad we took my friend there this time.  We loved our dishes so much that they were probably the best foods we had during her visit. We had deep fried chicken wings, tong choy (water spinach), rare beef filet with anchovies and deep fried crab meat rolls.  I could eat the chicken wings and crab meat rolls all day long.  Al;though deep fried, the wings and rolls were light in texture but also full of flavours at the same time. The slightly sweet undertone in the coating of the chicken wing batter was addictive. We came here on a Monday morning shortly after 1100 when they open and we walked right in.  By 1130, there were already people waiting for tables at the door.

Never bored of this place except the need to queue for a table. Chicken wings and Butter beef are must have. This time round discovered the lotus roots were a delight and the cuttlefish balls (too hungry and forgot photo) were chewy and tasty too. Glad I decided to run home after.

Visited about 3 weeks ago on vacation with family. Service was great, we didnt make a reservation but probably should have. The hostess was very helpful, seated us when the table was ready, helped take our orders and helped us decide what to order when we were torn between a few items. The food came out quickly and everything was delicious. The pork chops were flavorful, fried chicken wings were really good, and the rest of the food did not disappoint!
Truly a must visit! Bo buc lac is so tasteful. The crispy chicken wings are crunchy with the perfect amount of saltiness. Service is fast too. Show up before they open, because there is a lineup!

Pretty good Vietnamese food and I really enjoyed beef soup. It s like Pho but better. The tenderness of the beef is very nice and it s marinated well. There is a wait so make sure you get here early for this good food. Highly recommend this place to eat in Chinatown.

I dont think Ive ever had Cambodian food before, but the restaurant totally lived up to its reputation. My fiancee and I split the butter beef, fried chicken wings, and oyster pancake. I loved every dish though the butter beef was definitely my favorite. The Vietnamese coffee was also tasty.

Popular menus in this restaurant are chicken wing and garlic butter beef. I am not really a big fan of cilantro. So I was scared to try garlic butter beef. But the taste was amazing Also don t forget to try chicken as well Food

I m a Vancouver local and have been coming here since I was a kid. Ate here tonight with out of town friends and Phnom Penh still has the best fried chicken wings in the city! I also loved this clam dish (see photo) and the oyster pancake dish too (not pictured)! We also ordered a plate of water spinach and it s so good. That veggie is so hard to cook (for me) so I love ordering it here! Everyone must try this place if they re visiting or live here! I don t eat beef much but the butter beef and the beef Luc lac are fan favorites too!

Loveeeeee everything was so good. We waited for an hour on the weekend at noon but you can leave your number and they ll text. The service was really fast. You must get the fried chicken and butter beef, best fried chicken I ve ever had.

The hype is real, Phnom Penh is definitely a must visit for food lovers. This is our 2nd visit in less than a month. On our first visit we tried the food vloggers  recommended dishes which are the Marinated Buttered Beef, Fillet Beef Luc Lac and their famous Deep Fried Garlic Chicken Wings. On our 2nd visit we ordered again the deep fried chicken wings, vietnamese spring rolls and their butterfly prawns. All the dishes are delicious.  Staffs are friendly, service is quick and atmosphere is great. We will definitely be back again to try their other dishes.
Extraordinary well made dishes, highly recommended for marinated butter beef and the fried chicken wings. The fry water spinach is also tasty with full of wok-hay.

Food was amazing, had an amazing dinner here with some friends that lives in Vancouver. They recommended the restaurant and it didnt disappoint Food portions were good, waiter is nice and checking up on us if we needed more food. Do note that it does get really busy around dinner time we had to wait about 45 minutes before we got a table but well worth the wait

Love to come here whenever Im in Chinatown! The food is fantastic. They have an extensive menu, but Ive liked everything Ive had so far. Would definitely recommend the Marinated Butter Beef and their Chicken Wings! There is normally a wait, even for lunch, so be prepared to wait.

The butter-beef was amazing - really good food! It was off putting though how the server demands for tips this was the only flaw. I think tips should not be asked for its really tacky when places do this!

Came all the way from Edmonton to have their signature butter beef, chicken wings, and oyster pancake. It was well worth the trip and the long wait line. Go early to get a table or the wait time can be an hour or more. Best time is 3pm after lunch rush and before dinner. Highly recommended!
Had the fried chicken wings and beef brisket noodles, it was sooo good. Will definitely be back again very soon!

A friend took us here to this restaurant when we visited Vancouver and it was quite the treat. The food was excellent all around and my whole family really enjoyed the durian milkshake. The chicken wings were my favourite. They also had a few stir fried options for the vegetarians as well (lotus stems, snow pea tips, etc...)

Cant go wrong with this resto. Weve been coming to this resto for over 10 years and their food quality has been so consistent. I think they decreased their portion size in the past couple of years to keep up with inflation, but regardless, everything is delicious. We order the usual: fried rice, chicken wings, deep fried squid, butter beef, and baby lotus stem (this is something new weve never ordered before and it was delish!!). Expect at least 2-hour wait if you come during peak time. If you come around 4pm, its usually 1 hour wait.

Amazing everything.  My friends and I come here yearly for the past 10years with a group of 10-14. The owner and staff are very accommodating and super friendly and helpful. Great place to be for  lunch or dinner!

Great food , great service you know the restaurant is good when there is always a wait for a table. Highly recommend the marinated butter beef if you can eat Rare beef. Coming from toronto we dont have this dish. 5 stars

I love this place, but it s pretty busy, rightfully so. All the dishes we ordered were delicious, but I d say the must try is the papaya salad and fried chicken wings. The fried chicken wings has a very crispy yet light batter, which is also quite flavourful. Chicken is moist on the inside and it s relatively simple, yet so good. I like how refreshing the papaya salad is - it s nice and crunchy, perfect for a hot day outside. Sour soup is more of a warm weather dish, but packed with flavour and one of my favourite soups. It has items like pineapple for sweetness, tomatoes make it a bit tart and it s quite hearty as well. Beef luc lac was okay, I remember the beef being better last time so it could be a one off  however, fried egg is a must! I wasn t a big fan of the noodles either, felt it was a bit too oily and lacked flavour, other people at the table enjoyed it though, so I m not sure. Tong choy was really good as well, good portion, right flavour and not over cooked. Overall, the food is great here. Price is also reasonable being around $25 per person. Service to food is relatively quick. I would make reso s if you re a larger party though, otherwise expect to wait! I d definitely try this place and find out for yourself if it s worth the hype!

We ate at Phnom Penh knowing that lines are long and of course, full house! We werent surprised. We waited patiently coz from what weve heard and watched -its so worth it. True enough, this restaurant has filled our tummies and made our hearts full!!! Sorry for my photos! And its incomplete as we were really so excoted to try everything we werent able to take photos of the other foood!!!!

Reiterating what most reviews have already commented, Phnom Penh is a must try for all Vietnamese and Cambodian food lovers. The trifecta of dishes (I.e chicken wings, beef luc lac and beef carpaccio) are what most people try on their 1st visit and often default to on their 10th re-visit. There is a great deal of hype for the three dishes mentioned; however, try them with no expectations and you will not be disappointed! Beware of long wait times throughout the weekend AND weekdays. If visiting with a large group of 7 or more, it would be preferred to reserve two weeks in advance to secure a table.

There is always a line here to get in but it is well worth the wait. Their fried chicken wings are the best wings Ive had anywhere else and they dont even focused on wings here. Their butter beef is a must try as you wont get this anywhere else.

This is an excellent restaurant serving south east Asian food. It was a 1 hr wait for our group which is a sign of how popular the restaurant is. We had #4 which was Mi Kho Nam Vang which was close to the Singaporean Back Chor Mee minus the black vinegar. This is a must try noodle dish. We also had the oyster omelette which was excellent. Lastly we had the chicken wings which was very well done. See my photos!

SO GOOD I WENT TWICE IN 24H! On our first encounter, we were told it was going to be a 2h wait for dinner (table of 4). Instead of waiting, we decided to get take out. We got the basil clams, tong choy, dry noodles, large chicken wings and com dac rice combo. The noodles werent the best since it was takeout and ended up being dry and bland. The clams were flavourful and you got a huge portion. The Com dac rice was good and the tong choy had good flavour. THE STAR OF THE SHOW WAS THE CHICKEN WINGS!!! Even after driving 45 min home in a takeout container the chicken wings were the best I ever had. In fact it was so good, we decided to try to come back to eat it in the restaurant. We ended up going back at 2pm the next day and still had to wait 45 min for a table of 3. We ordered the chicken wings and the butter beef. The butter beef had good spicy flavor and we also ordered the beef bo luc lac which was moist and flavourful. Overall highly recommend, the wait is worth it!
Food was amazing, but surprisingly busy at 3pm on a Sunny Sunday! Well worth the 30- 45 min wait. Had the Beef combacha, lemon grass pork and chicken wings.
The hype is real in this Bib Gourmand restaurant! Food was so good. I can eat a whole plate of the chicken wings. Be prepared to wait if you wanna try but the wait is worth it!
The only downside is needing to get a reservation or waiting for a table - its that good. The food was very much worth it. Chicken wings are incredible.

An institution in Vancouver, Phnom Penh is a must try for anyone visiting Vancouver. My brother used to live in Vancouver and brought me here years ago, and it didnt disappoint the second time around. Recommend the butter beef, and while I didnt get it this time, the chicken wings are very good here. Make a reservation or be prepared to wait! Theres always a long wait for this restaurant.

I ve been coming to Phnom Penh for over a decade and introduced many friends to this restaurant. Prices are still reasonable considering how popular it is. Our go-to order: Stew Beef Rice Noodle, Beef Lu Lac with Rice (no egg because we re cheap), Fried Chicken Wings (Large  trust me). When I want to treat myself I add: Rare beef (again, trust me, it s SO good) and a Moo Moo Shake. The stew beef soup has a perfect hint of sweetness from the carrot and beef. Beef luc lac is simple and perfect for picky eaters. The chicken wings are even more famous than rare beef, crunchy with a hint of sweetness - but it s the lemon pepper sauce that keeps you craving more. Every time I taste the sauce I want to pull a Plankton and sneak in their kitchen for the secret recipe. During today s visit, a bug kept flying around my plate and got stuck in my rice. We asked for a new plate to use - the young server was professional and took it really seriously, even offering to replace the whole original dish but we reassured him it was just my own plate. He checked in with us through our meal and even brought us a delicious tapioca taro dessert because he felt bad about the bug in my food. He made our experience 110% better - to note, the general service staff are friendly all around. Legends about the wait times are true: even on a Monday evening your wait for 2 will be 30-40 minutes. When it s busy, expect anywhere from 1-2 hours. Leave your # and they ll text you to confirm once a table is available. They only take resos for 8+ group sizes. FYI their washroom and tap water is notoriously cold, try to avoid it in the winter time!

You will not find another Cambodian/Vietnamese restaurant in Vancouver that will make your mouth water like Phnom Penh. It is a go to spot for many, and rightfully so. Highly recommend the following for first timers as a must have: chicken wings, luc luc beef, and butter beef. Having tried a variety of other items on the menu, it s safe to say there s not one dish where I would not get again or would not recommend. If you re looking for a home style, authentic Asian restaurant, this is the place.

This restaurant makes absolutely delicious dishes! The best pork bone soup ever. The service was not overly friendly, but we do not mind - they are always extremely busy. The atmosphere was okay, but the food was so good that all the little things fade away. Delish!
Michelin star twice in a row 2022 & 2023. Very good food.

Delicious food for a family-style meal. Our group favourites were the deep fried wings, butter beef and the spring rolls. Good service. Lovely tea as well. Vegetarian options: They had a vegetarian noodle soup and some other options.

There is a reason this place is packed! Food is consistent and never disappoints. Our latest trip had us waiting 1.5 hours (arrived at 6:30pm, seated at 8pm - our names were put on a waitlist, and a text message sent to you when your table is ready) Highlights are: Chicken Wings (it s Garlicky. With a lemon pepper sauce) Butter Beef (Asian take on a beef carpaccio) Beef Luc Lac Trieu Chau Fried Rice (Teochew Fried Rice)
Very best of Phnom Penh noodles, rolls, soups, pork chops, oyster, fish balls and everything.

Phnom Penh was at the top of our wish list for our trip to Vancouver and I m glad we got a chance to eat here. This place lives up to the hype and awards it has earned. Even at odd hours in between lunch and dinner this place still had a waitlist going but luckily we were seated after 15 minutes waiting around. The interior gives cozy mom and pop vibes and the menu is pretty extensive. My recommendations are the fried chicken wings which come in a small or large serving and have a delicious salty breading with a peppery dipping sauce, as well as the fried beef with egg on top of a bed of fried rice. The fried rice was something else with so many amazing flavors all combined into one dish.

Reservations: no reservations under 6 ppl. However, only one person from your party needs to get you on the texting wait list. They estimated 15-20 min but it only took 10 min. During the wait, there is a book store across the street and a vintage clothing store down the block. I d recommend Fat Mao thai noodle house down the street if the wait is too long. Food: The Butter Beef (raw beef) brought a surprising freshness to the meal - cilantro and citrus. I d order an egg on top of the Beef Luc Lac next time. I would order everything again + the #4 next time because so many people around us ordered it. The atmosphere is like a busier Chinatown BBQ. Fast service, hot food, kind staff. This place has been around for a long time! I d highly recommend it.
Great food with fast serving speed. Everything tastes    and my fav is luc lac rice and Crab roll. Only thing is it took too long to get a seat in. Remember to join waitlist as early as possible

Chicken wings: 8.510 (skip the sauce! Use sauce from stir fry instead)!! Stir fry beef over rice: 9/10 Butter beef: 9/10 Service: 9/10 lovely ppl Atmosphere: 9/10 your classic loud Asian restaurant! Come back! Worth the wait. If you come at 6pm , you ll be seated around 715! Don t think you can make reservations, so either come at 4/5 or prepare to wait for 1 hr!!

I like the BBQ pork! It s super tasty!! -No reservations so recommend to get there have a waiting list first then when they re ready they will text you! -came here around 2pm on Friday Waiting time is around 30 minutes

Super flavorful dishes, each one significantly stands out! The owners and servers are super duper friendly. Heard the stories of the whole origin and start of Phnom Penh, totally inspiring and bafflingly amazing! Must try restaurant in Vancouver! The wings are the best
Amazing, super long wait but worth it. The fried rice and the raw beef dish tasted out of this world!! Definitely recommended

Exquisite! Everything I ve had here so far has been excellent and I am eager to eventually try everything on the menu. If you love Asian food and cilantro you won t be disappointed here. Try to go in a big group, and 100% share so you can try as many things as possible. When I went at 1pm on a Monday, there was a 30 min wait and when I went again, wanting more, on the following Thursday at 11:20 there was no wait.

Whenever I m in Vancouver, I always drop by and managed to get lucky without having to wait in line or get seated within 5-10 mins. Love the dry egg noodle soup with their fried chicken! Of course you gotta try the Marinated Butter Beef and Filet Beef Luc Lac! As someone from Cambodia, I would hit up this place whenever I crave for Cambodian food!

Epic - the more I think about this place the better it gets. Certainly will be returning. Possibly for take out to avoid the wait. Great prices, high quality food. Staff cares. Butter beef, Spicy squid, Chicken wings, Beef salad rolls, Sweet and Sour soup, Papaya salad and Lemon grass chicken. Only small sizes as this was heaps of food.
Cant go wrong with this restaurant. The quality is as good as it has always been... and the line up will always be there, so be prepared.

One of the best selections in Vietnamese cuisine ! Its worth the wait cause at anytime of day they are always busy! Unless you book ahead but it has to be 5 or more that your allowed to book reservation, anything less first come first serve! Chicken wings and beef tar tar is a must order! Enjoy everyone!!

One of the best restaurants in Vancouver, well received among foodie blogs/videos, finally got to try it on a weekday with no lineup. I tried a few dishes that are not popular, just to see if they are good at other dishes too, and they didn t disappoint. All the dishes I tried were good. The deep fried prawn balls are good, so bouncy, and cooked just right, still juicy on the inside. Prawn supreme wrapped in sugar cane were the bomb, not every Vietnamese restaurant offer that, and they made it so well, prawn combined with the sweetness of the sugar cane takes the flavour profile to the next level. I will order this dish again, even it s $17 for 2 pieces Service was good in Chinese/Asian standard. One of the best in the city, can t wait to try other dishes

Phnom Penh serves exceptionally scrumptious and unique Cambodian & Vietnamese dishes which will suit any food lovers taste. Every dish is hearty and enjoyable. My team and I arrived around 3:30 pm and waited less than 30 minutes to be seated. The waiting system is convenient as we left phone numbers for the restaurant to contact us when our table was available. Phnom Penh was definitely busy with lots of customers but there were a lot of servers who were pretty much available whenever needed. We ordered Marinated Butter Beef, Deep-Fried Chicken Wings (Large Size), Bo Luc Lac, Dry Noodles (can choose egg or rice) and Spicy Squid. Every dish was so distinctively marinated and cooked. The portions are not huge but average, except for the Marinated Butter Beef which I hope was bigger as it is a dish that only you can enjoy in Phnom Penh. Both fried chicken wings and squid were nicely fried without being too greasy. Please do not be hesitant to visit Phnom Penh for amazing Cambodian & Vietnamese dishes as it is definitely worth the wait and experience!

The food is sooo good here!! Its always busy so even if you get there for an earlier dinner itll be busy. Make sure your entire party is there. We ordered the dry egg noodles (4), stew beef egg noodles (8), filet beef luc lac on rice with egg (35), canh chia ca (45), marinated butter beef (71), deep fried chicken wings (78), spicy squid (79). All of these are our favourites! Highly recommend!

I ve been going here since the 80s, and came coming here in 2023 brought back so many memories. The staff hasn t aged, is still as friendly, and the food is still top notch. I always order  number 2  on the menu, and the oyster cake and durian dessert is amazing.

I went to 3 oclock , we waited for about an hour for a table. They text you when your table is ready. We got the garlic fried chicken wings, ,dry noodle, spring roll and f butter beef  loved them all! Best restaurant in Vancouver!!!
great food, very busy restaurant, reso for parties of 6+ only, walk-in wait is 1h, food is served very quickly, must flag waiters for them to see you, expect to yell across the table for conversation

This is my favourite Vietnamese/Cambodian restaurant in the city. The food is always consistent and delicious. I highly Recommend Marinated Beef Butter and Papaya Salad! I can eat that salad every day. Must try !
Food is always delicious!  We order famous chicken wings every time.  It s a must!  Only complaint is the lineup. That s why we order takeout.  Chicken wings are crispy when we get home.

When an old Vietnamese restaurant gets a Michelin star, they either rest on their laurels or continue to deliver exceptional food and service.   I can joyfully report the food is amazing and the service impeccable.

Opened in the 1980s, this place is a must visit just for its history. Be sure to get here early as you can expect to wait for a table for at least 30 mins. Their popular chicken wings are a must try. My favorite was the fried rice, generous portions. The dry mixed noodles were also highly recommended.

Small, authentic Cambodian/Vietnamese restaurant. The papaya salad with shrimps, beef jerky and peanuts was fresh and delicious. Free jasmine tea !. Mind that waiting can be long (40min late evening), but worth it . Would recommend it to anyone visiting; *** be careful when walking there from downtown, could be sketchy.
Some of the best food Ive ever had. Highly recommend the fried chicken, butter beef and Cambodian soup. Vegetarian options: Plentiful
Very authentic dishes crab  , beef, vietnamese coffee ..all At reasonable price too! Will def go again! Food : 5/5
good food. Good quality and quantity. We were forced to check the bill and leave at last though.

Ordered the butter beef and the house special chicken wing. The beef was presented beautifully and had in it all the great flavours of south asian cuisine, the wings were well fried made with a light batter making it still moist on the inside and crispy on the outside. Great experience and look forward to it again.

I have been going to this restaurant for years! And most recently I ve enjoyed seeing a great improvement of their level of service. This place got a Michelin nod and I m not surprised. Their chicken wings are hands down the best in the city.  Other must haves dishes are the butter beef, shrimp fried rice, baby lotus stems, and the mango moo moo shake. Definitely worth visiting if you can get in, and definitely worth the wait.

This place has really good fried chicken wings! They give you some pretty good lemon juice/sauce to pair with it, and you get about 8 pieces (or 4 whole wings), if you buy a small. I also got the spring roll, which was decent (though, I dont think thats their main attraction; I just wanted some vegetables). I think I need to visit again, and very some of their beef dishes, since they also seem popular. The only drawback here is that you will have a long wait. Its not super insane, but I had to wait maybe 45min on the waitlist to get seated.

Loved the fried chicken wings. As others mentioned, the food was solid, but not sure if it was mind-blowing enough for a 40 minute wait. Regardless, service was good and the price was good for such a popular restaurant!

I have no idea if Phnom Penh changed the way they take reservations and walkins but the way they treated our group on a Saturday night was absolutely spectacular. For the regular restaurant goers, this place is always packed and has a hefty line. At first when we went we thought it would be a rush in and out as it usually is but our server very kindly told us that we had an allotted time and to not worry and to not rush instead reassuring us to take our time. For a place as busy as this it was an odd and refreshing experience to know that we had extra time to digest a meal and enjoy ourselves. I hope this doesn t make any newbies scared to go however it s just a common thing in any restaurant to kind of eat get your bill and then leave rather than chat up for three hours over 1 cup of coffee. Usually the trifecta is the beef luc lac, butter beef and chicken wings - but this time it only felt satisfactory instead of the star acts. The wings weren t as plump and juicy and the luc lac was just regular. That being said - it s hard to not order the favourites, just a bit of a different dining experience than usual for Those dishes. We also ordered the oyster pancake (crispy and light), fried rice cake (kind of like a mix between radish cake and tteokbokki with a delicious and flavourful dipping sauce) and pea tips (you know - to get those veggies in). For dessert we also ordered the taro pudding which was a nice ending and very starchy (naturally duh) so it was perfect to share between the 6 of us instead of each ordering a dish. They also still have their birthday option where they turn the lights off in the whole restaurant sings happy birthday as the stuffing in the cake which is always nice. The staff are nice here - they wore masks as of December 3rd and are very attentive. There is a small  waiting area  inside the restaurant so most groups are asked to wait outside - dress accordingly in case those lines are long! Groups of 6 can call ahead for reservations and are subject to 18% gratuity (of course confirm with them as these reviews have info subject to change). Phnom Penh is one of our fav places to go for comfort food.

What can I say. The absolute best chicken wings Ive ever tasted. Not only are their wings wonderfully tasty, but all the other dishes we ordered were 100000/10. Our group of 6 came here on a Saturday evening. The wait for a table ended up being 90 minutes. We took a menu while waiting so we knew what to order right away. Once we were seated, we placed our order and surprisingly the food came out in less than 5 minutes. The servers kindly changed out our dishes to help with cleanliness and the remaining bones from the wings. Dishes were ordered were: stew beef in hot pot (wonderful beef slices and tendons with melt in your mouth carrots), papaya salad (so refreshing), marinated butter beef (absolutely yum), spicy squid (so juicy), a beef dish over lettuce (cant remember the name), and a shrimp noodle dish. Ive heard good things about the beef luc lac! What an amazing restaurant.

Phnom Penh is a very, very busy, bustling restaurant. It is located in Chinatown of Vancouver, BC, on East Georgia. You can definitely find crowds of people lining up to dine at this restaurant. We decided to order take-out instead of dining in just because it was so busy tonight. The food still came out great, and we still came out happy. We ordered their famous fried chicken wings, Phnom Penh Deep-fried Chicken Wings, 2 orders of their Filet Beef Luc Lac on Rice with Eggs, and the Marinated Butter Beef also known as, Marinated Thit Bo. My boyfriend and I would have to rate this restaurant a 5/5. One, for their quality of food, two, for their service, and three, for their politeness. Although it was super busy, the gentleman helping us remembered our orders and was very courteous. Thank you, Phnom Penh! I would definitely recommend this restaurant for others to come and dine when it is not quite busy or even have it ordered for take-out. It is worth the try!

Went there for a lunch and to try the famous chicken wings and it didnt dissapoint. Its so good and the beef luc lac with egg on rice is a must too. The vietnamese ice coffee is also a nice addition for your meal.
My first time at the Vietnamese spot was awesome! The food rocked, especially bo tai chanh
Great food and super nice staff. 100% recommend. Chicken wings, beef luc lac, butter beef

So yummy! We (3 people) ordered large chicken wings, rice noodle soup, butter beef, and BBQ lemongrass chicken on rice.  Portions weren t too big so 4 dishes were adequate for the 3 of us. The chicken wings are PHENOMENAL - sweet & crispy!! The restaurant seems to use a lot of cilantro on most of their dishes, which I love! We went on Monday around 7PM and there was a 15 minute wait. Would return just for the chicken wings!

We were thrilled to find Phnom Penh open on New Year s day and went on to order takeout of few dishes we had not tried before. Sausage fried rice was a really hearty bowl as expected, but I was really curious about Cha Kappip under Kitchen Suggestions. The main element in the dish is ground pork in fried shrimp and chili paste accompanied by lettuce, cabbage, tomatoes, and cucumber sliced Tear a piece of the green and add a proportionate amount of pork on it. Top with a tomato slice. Both the crunchiness of lettuce/cabbage against the pork and the sourness of tomato result in a perfect bite. Garlic prawns is also highly recommended. The salty-garlicky prawn goodness under that crispy outer layer makes you go back for more.

Went on a Wednesday at 5 PM - had a 15 min wait MAX; the line was definitely longer as it approached dinner time. Never had a more efficient service experience in my life. Food was served within 7 minutes of ordering. Deep-fried chicken wings (#78) were amazing and must-tries. Marinated butter beef (#71) not my personal favourite because of the strength of the sauce, but would recommend trying. Beef luc lac was very good, and is a safe option.
Great food, everything is amazing on the menu.  Staff is super friendly.  Never been disappointed here.

Phnom Penh is a popular Vietnamese & Cambodian restaurant in the heart of the city, known for their marinated butter beef. The restaurant is usually busy, but the wait is worth it as the food is delicious. The beef is cooked to perfection and is served with a side of rice and vegetables. The meal is hearty and satisfying, and the service is friendly and efficient. The restaurant is definitely worth a visit if youre looking for a good vietnamese meal.

After 12 years of living in Vancouver, I finally tried this place out. Can confirm: the chicken wings are bomb. Shared a few dishes here and all of it was delicious. I would highly reccommend stopping by if you re in the area! It was a 40 minute wait for 3 people.. be sure to plan for that!

Very popular Vietnamese place. We went at an odd hour but the restaurant was still full. The food is amazing especially the fried chicken wings. A must order. The white pepper dipping sauce makes all the difference. The portion is decent and the service is quick but can t say they re attentive. They also have a lotta take out orders. Generally a very busy restaurant.

I am SO happy I was able to squeeze this glorious place into my YVR itinerary. First thing I ll say I liked about this place is that they were one of very few restaurants that had an automated waitlist with text notifications! You d think in a busy tourist city like Vancouver more places would have this. Upon entry, you are greeted with the most divine smell of Vietnamese and Cambodian cuisine. I can t even put into words how good it smells in there. Excited as ever, we started with the Fried Chicken Wings and Garlic Fried Shrimp and  God in heaven. I don t know what they put in those or how they cook these items but WOW. I ve never had anything that can compare to how delicious these are. The wings were definitely the star of this show but the shrimp came pretty close. Both were so crispy, savoury and real garlicky! I also really loved the sort of lemon dipping sauce that comes with the wings. For entrees we ordered Filet Beef Luc Lac with Egg and Phnom Penh Jumbo Rice with Pork Chops. The Jumbo Rice was pretty good, the pork chops were undoubtedly well seasoned. BUT THE BEEF LUC LAC?????? Phenomenal. This dish was literally the perfect balance of sweet and savoury. The beef was so delicious, and when mixed together with the vegetables and egg yolk- heavenly. I really enjoyed the underlying coconut flavour in the dish as well. I also tried some of their Black Peppered Squid and it was yummy too! Not only was the food good, but the service was too. Our food was prepared in lightening speed, so it really made up for the 30 minute wait to be seated. Honestly, I m so glad I came here and it would have really been a shame if I missed out on such a place. Phnom Penh is truly a MUST stop in Vancouver.

Long wait but Great food!! Absolutely in love with the fried chicken! - hu tieu mi bo kho (beef noodle stew) - fried spring rolls - fried chicken - lemongrass pork chop set (with shredded pork, ham & rice)

Delicious, and well worth the wait. Be sure to get there early, put your name and number down for a table, and plan to browse the neighbourhood for 1-1.5 hrs before you get seated... But its worth it, I promise!

Best Viet restaurant I have been to in my life. A friend recommended this place and I am so happy I was able to try this place because the food is amazing. So many delicious flavours! We got the papaya salad and I believe it was #80 beef with bean sprouts. The portion sizes are quite large so I would say the food is quite reasonably priced even on the cheaper side. I highly recommend this place!

Absolutely delicious food. Our absolute favorite were the Chicken Wings (we liked it without the lemon pepper sauce... Good thing they put that on the side), the Beef Luc Lac and of course their famous Butter Beef!! Will definately be back.

I really liked the place! Visited on Sunday at lunchtime. The wait was shorter than expected. They have a good system with callback so that you can walk around in Chinatown instead of crowding in the waiting area. The food was excellent! The fried chicken wings and Butter beef (dont let the name fool you - its actually thin raw beef in marinade) were recommended as their specialty and they were great! And to top that the service was genuinely friendly and helpful. Thank you!

A must go in Vancouver. Order the holy trinity - butter beef, chicken wings, and bo luc lac with an egg. We ventured into other things, like pho, hu tieu nam vang kho (dry noodles mushroom sauce), and hu tieu Bo kho but I d stick to the  holy trinity ! I also like their moo moo shakes!

Amazing food and service. The famous chicken wings here are legit. The food is always on point. It s one of those places where it s hard to come here regularly because of the wait, honestly. It s not a place you would walk by and think of just strolling in for food. You need to plan the wait time in advance. If the wait doesn t bother you then the food is worth the wait. Prices are reasonable. Ambiance is a bit dated in general but the real star is the food.
Vancouver one of the best restaurants. location is inside of China town Food

The menu is extensive and uniquely curated with Cambodian/Vietnamese/Teochow dishes. My first experience with this fusion and it didnt disappoint. The butter beef was the absolute show stopper. Although the line was fairly quick for a Friday evening, I would wait an hour for it if I had to. Outstanding restaurant!
Place was full and buzzing even at afternoon around 3:30 pm. Everything was delicious and price is reasonable! Chicken wings and marinated beef were highights.
Chicken wings is out all-time favorite!! My bf and I are 7 wings by ourselves and still craving for more  their beef is so good is a must try!!

To say Phnom Penh is a staple in the Vancouver restaurant scene is an understatement. Always popular and always pleasing for a reason... The food is so comforting. From the famous chicken wings to the melt-in-your-mouth butter beef to the simplicity of fried rice with Chinese sausage... You cant go wrong. We came by in early December and dine-in was a little less busy than in the past (covid related no doubt) but picked up as we were finishing. Some other recommendations to try here is the Beef Luc Lac (you can either get a small order served with rice and a fried egg or get a large serving by itself and pair it with a full dish of fried rice). The squid here is similar to the addictive chicken wings and is often overlooked but worth the try. If it wasnt so darn cold out, we would have picked up one of their tasty moo shakes.

Delicious food and quick service. Highly recommend butter beef and fried chicken wings. There is always a line so go early or expect to wait. I arrived 5-10 mins after 11AM (when they open) and it was already packed. I waited 45 minutes. Street paid parking available outside and washrooms are on the second level. Stalls are clean.

The best meal I had from my visit to Vancouver! We heard about this place from other friends and just had to try it because its hard to find Cambodian food in Calgary. We got the garlic fried chicken wings, butter beef (rare beef), and fillet beef luc lac rice and loved them all! They are only doing takeout right now so its good to place your order over the phone first so you wont have to wait as long. Even then you may find people waiting for their order when you arrive.

Heard about this place from a bunch of friends but never had the chance to give them a try because they are always busy, but with COVID, they switch to takeout so was finally able to order some food to try.  The wings, were nice and crispy and garlicky, super tasty and addicting.  The marinated butter beef was delicious.  The beef was super soft and the sauce and topping was perfect.  Hopefully by the time I can visit YVR again they are opening for dinning in again and I will be able to try a number of other items on their menu.

The chicken wings were delicious as usual, and the marinated butter beef came in a large portion. I recommend the baby lotus stems, which are juicy and flavourful, as well as the dry egg noodles, which come with complimentary pork bone soup.
Top notch food for great value!  Always great to order the butter beef, chicken wings and radish cakes!  Even with a 1hr lineup at peak times its worth the wait.
